<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-19"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-19')">19</a>. I'm not exactly a slouch, considering I was bred to become a thief. But thanks anyways. ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-20"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-20')">20</a>. I mean, hey, if it pisses off the Gun-toting Organization of Cretins, I'm down with that. ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-21"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-21')">21</a>. ROCK WAR. Say it with me, &quot;ROCK WAR.&quot; ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-22"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-22')">22</a>. Does anyone know how the fuck this makes sense? Do they expect you to wrestle a living rock for thirty seconds? Just run circles around the bastard. ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-23"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-23')">23</a>. While this may seem unnerving, please understand that research shows they can burst through carbonized steel at speeds up to one hundred thirty kilometers per hour. As they show a near-complete lack of ability to change direction or stopping when moving beyond sixty kilometers per hour, we strongly recommend dropping down and acting dead. ~ G.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-24"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-24')">24</a>. The disappearance of Nevryn's library card as well as a few other Jailor documents may be attributed to them. Further investigation is required. ~ G.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-25"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-25')">25</a>. Jeez, and you call me rude. ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-26"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-26')">26</a>. Hey, you cut out the rest of the quote! I gave a fifteen minute rant about how boring the fights were, and this is how you repay me? ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-27"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-27')">27</a>. Wait, in that case, doesn't the entire document have to be revised, considering how half of it assumes they are the same? ~ N.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-28"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-28')">28</a>. Considering how lax the Jailors have been after prolonged exposure to the Arrogance entities, it cannot be ruled out that this pacifism is a facade meant to lull them into a false sense of security. ~ G.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-29"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-29')">29</a>. I understand that this may be an overly dramatic end for our article. In the past few iterations I had this earlier in the document and some editors complained that the &quot;escalation was off,&quot; whatever that means. In any case, seeing as there is a massive power struggle among the various groups of interest around the arena, we feel it would be prudent not to fall into this potential trap. ~ G.</div>
